Notes.en-us:
⚠️ Warning: This is a Shared File

Normally you would add settings to images which belong to a specific thing, like images which belong to a blog-post. This file is shared, so it could be used in many places. The settings you edit here will apply everywhere this file used.
Notes.de-de:
⚠️Warnung: Gemeinsam genutzte Datei

Normalerweise setzt man Einstellungen bei Bildern, die zu einem bestimmten Ding gehören, beispielsweise Bilder eines Blog-Beitrags. Diese Datei ist global und kann an vielen Orten verwendet werden. Diese Einstellungen gelten auch, wenn diese Datei anderswo eingesetzt wird.

Notes.en-us:
Configure Presets on a Field, like the default Resize and Lightbox behavior on

  • WYSIWYG fields
  • Image fields
  • Image Library fields

These presets will be picked up automatically by the API such as ImageService.Img(...) and ImageService.Picture(...) as well as the .Html(...) method.
Describe your image for screen readers and SEO.
Notes.de-de: Beschreibe dein Bild für Menschen mit Behinderungen und Google / SEO.

TitleFalse.en-us: Use a default title (as none is specified here)
TitleFalse.de-de: Verwende Standardbeschriftung (da hier keine angegeben wurde)

Notes.en-us: This is only shown in special scenarios like when used in galleries.
Notes.de-de: Dies wird nur in speziellen Fällen angezeigt, beispielsweise in Galerien.

Notes.en-us: Specify how the image should be cropped if it is automatically resized.
Notes.de-de: Gib an wie das Bild zugeschnitten werden soll, wenn es automatisch angepasst wird.

DropdownValues.en-us:
:Default Crop - Use image as the template expects it, usually crop to center
none:Don't Crop - the entire image should be visible
to:Corner or Side Crop - the most important part is in a corner or on a side

:🎯 Default - Center
tl:↖️ Top Left
tc:⬆️ Top Center
tr:↗️ Top Right
ml:⬅️ Middle Left
mc:🎯 Middle Center
mr:➡️ Middle Right
bl:↙️ Bottom Left
bc:⬇️ Bottom Center
br:↘️ Bottom Right

Notes.en-us: Override the resize settings on this image.
Notes.de-de: Verwende eigene Einstellungen für die Anzeigegrösse dieses Bildes.

Notes.en-us: Tip: Crop settings will only take effect if the template creating the HTML interprets the settings. If it seems like the settings don't work, please contact your web developer.
Notes.de-de: Tipp: Die Einstellungen wirken nur, wenn das Template (der Teil, welches HTML generiert) diese berücksichtigt. Sollten die Einstellungen nicht wirken, dann frag deinen Webdesigner.

Notes.en-us: For help, see docs.
Images in the same lightbox group will work together like an album.
Notes.de-de: Bilder in der selben Lightbox-Gruppe funktionieren gemeinsam wie ein Album.

DropdownValues.en-us:
:No Group - this image will open stand alone
default:Default Group - all images in this group will be in an album together
DropdownValues.de-de:
:Keine Gruppe - dieses Bild öffnet alleine
default:Standard Gruppe - alle Bilder in dieser Gruppe sind wie ein Album

Formula.en-us: v1(data, context) { return data.CropBehavior == 'to'; }
v1(data, context) { return data.CropBehavior !== ''; }

Notes.en-us:
The View-Configuration is only for configuring URL parameters. 

As of now, it doesn't support configuring alternate durations.

Your code may return different results based on URL parameters. If this is the case, then you want to vary by URL parameters. 

⚠️ Warning: Be careful with this configuration. If you don't specify which url parameters are allowed, you can easily build up tens of thousands of cache entries which may slow down your system.

Name.en-us: Cache By Url Parameters (for blogs etc. which have different pages)

TitleFalse.en-us: Use same cache even if URL parameters change

TitleTrue.en-us: Use new cache if URL parameter changes

TitleFalse.en-us: Url parameters are NOT case-sensitive: A=a, É=é (recommended)

TitleTrue.en-us: Url parameters are case sensitive: A≠a & É≠é

Name.en-us: URL Parameter Names (one on each line)

Notes.en-us: Put each url parameter on an own line. Optionally with // comment behind it. * means all url parameters - not recommended ⚠️.

Placeholder.en-us: example     // vary the cache by the url parameter example=abcd

TitleFalse.en-us: If other url parameters are used, cache as if they don't matter

TitleTrue.en-us: If other url parameters are used, don't cache

Description.en-us: Configure what Metadata is expected on something

EditInstructions.en-us:
This configures what Metadata is expected on this kind of item. It's mainly used to help create toolbars automatically. 

Important: This wil not prevent other metadata, but simply make work easier.

Title.en-us: Mark a Content-Type to expect a specific Metadata

Notes.en-us: Determines what exactly expects this target.
How many of these are expected, typically 1. Use a large number like 100 to indicated lots. 0 means it shouldn't be used, so the UI can show a warning.

Description.en-us: Mark a Content-Type as being Metadata for a specific target type (App, Content-Type etc.)

EditInstructions.en-us: Used to decorate Content-Types to tell them what they usually describe.

0:Not set
2:Field Definition (Attribute) - not supported yet

4:Entity (Item)

Notes.en-us: How many of these are expected, typically 1. Use a large number like 100 to indicated lots. 0 means it shouldn't be used, so the UI can show a warning.
Special warning to show when deleting. Use this for primary-metadata like content-type description.

Description.en-us: Mark a Content-Type to allow empty-items to be saved.

EditInstructions.en-us:
By default, content-types without fields would result in empty items, and they would not be saved. 

Use this decorator to mark a content-type which should save items even if they are completely empty.
